Over 20 gospel artistes are set to thrill Nigerians at the maiden edition of the Seraph Youth Mega Praise concert today at the National Stadium in Surulere, Lagos. The musical event, tagged: “Praising God in beauty of His holiness”, has been described as the largest gathering in the history of the church as over 20,000 youths are expected to attend. At a news conference to mark the event, Rev. Mother Abimbola Esther Ajayi said she got the vision from God through to be executed by the youths of Cherubim and Seraphim Church. She said: “This mega praise reminds us of how we can win our battles with our weapon of praise. The concert is to create an atmosphere of praise and give glory to God for His love towards us as the year is ending, and to get set for a new beginning. We are also encouraged as Christians to praise God at all times, irrespective of any situation we find ourselves. “It is also essential to bring together all Christian youths, irrespective of denomination, and foster unity.” The cleric, however, admonished the Federal Government to declare a day as “National Praise Day” where all Nigerians, irrespective of religion or tribe, will come together in unison to appreciate the kindness of God. Artistes billed to lead the praise include Tope Alabi, Esther Igbekele, Lanre Teriba, Aduke Gold, Bisi Alawiye, Dare Melody, Azadus, Bunmi Akinnanu, Rachael Ogunyemi and many others. Also, comedians like Kenny Blaq and Woli Agba will grace the event. There will be free transportation at specific locations within the city to convey attendees. 